creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 148 by Various.
Read in English by Shakira Searle; SkyAlbatross; Michele Fry; Newgatenovelist; Winston Tharp; Bruce Kachuk; Tony Addison; Melissa Hoffman; Leonard Wilson; Peter Tucker; David Wales; Son of the Exiles
This is a collection of 27 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for September 2015.
After Parting, by Sara Teasdale At Night, by Sara Teasdale Before a Painting, by James Weldon Johnson The Changeling, by James Russell Lowell Earth to Earth, by Michael Field The Emperor of Ice-Cream, by Wallace Stevens Enough, by Sara Teasdale The Final Tax, by Ellis Parker Butler Kashmiri Song by Juma, by Laurence Hope Kubla Khan, by Samuel Taylor Coleridge The London Bobby, by Ella Wheeler Wilcox For I Will Consider My Cat Jeoffry, by Christopher Smart Natural Selection, by Constance Naden Night in the City, by Ellis Parker Butler I’m an Old Black Kettle, by Louisa May Alcott Persuasions to Joy: a Song, by Thomas Carew Peter Quince at the Clavier, by Wallace Stevens Praise and Prayer, by William Davenant A Question, by Ellis Parker Butler The Reeds of Runnymede, by Rudyard Kipling Sir Patrick Spens, by Anonymous They Flee From Me, by Thomas Wyatt Thirteen Ways of Looking at a Blackbird, by Wallace Stevens Time, by Jasper Mayne To America, by James Weldon Johnson Two Little Shadows, by Anonymous The Wantaritencant, by Henry Lawson For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
